 {"id":"bd-2o55","title":"Demo Showcase: Accessibility Modes","description":"## Background

A jaw-dropping demo still needs to be usable.

This feature provides accessibility modes that apply *uniformly* across the showcase:
- high contrast
- reduced motion
- large text / spacing

Done right, it also stress-tests the theme/token system and the animation system.

## UX / Core Interactions

- A small "A11y" panel with toggles:
  - High contrast
  - Reduced motion
  - Large text
- Immediate application to the whole app.
- Optional: persisted mode in demo state.

Suggested keybindings:
- A: toggle A11y panel
- H: high contrast
- M: reduced motion
- L: large text

## Architecture Notes

- High contrast:
  - implemented as a theme variant or a constraint-enforced palette adjustment
  - enforce WCAG AA (or stronger) in unit tests

- Reduced motion:
  - animation system must expose a global "motion scale" (0..1)
  - when disabled, animations stop deterministically (no half-frames)

- Large text:
  - scale typography tokens and spacing tokens
  - ensure layout remains stable and does not overflow disastrously

## Acceptance Criteria

- Toggles apply immediately and deterministically.
- High contrast mode passes contrast tests.
- Reduced motion mode disables animations in a verifiable way.
- Large text mode remains usable in 80x24.

Additionally (project-wide standards):
- Alien Artifact: define invariants + failure modes; if heuristics exist, specify an explainable decision rule (evidence ledger / Bayes factors where applicable)
- Extreme Optimization: baseline -> profile -> opportunity matrix; for each perf change include an isomorphism proof + golden output checksums
- Unit tests: happy path + edge cases + regression fixtures; add property tests for core invariants where applicable
- E2E: scripts with verbose JSONL logging (env, capabilities, timings, seed, checksums) + deterministic mode

## Alien Artifact Upgrades (Concrete)

- Contrast constraint solving:
  - treat palette selection as a constrained optimization problem in a perceptual space (OKLCH)
  - prove contrast bounds in tests for all semantic swatches

## Extreme Optimization

- Mode toggles must be O(1) per frame (no rebuilding large structures per frame).
- Add a regression test for mode toggle latency (bd-2o55.2).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-02T22:30:54.843366513Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-03T19:11:00.074284039Z","closed_at":"2026-02-03T19:11:00.074261216Z","close_reason":"All 6 subtasks completed: snapshot/golden tests, transition regression tests, unit tests, E2E PTY tests, diagnostic logging, and UX/A11y review all closed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["accessibility","demo","ux"],"comments":[{"id":377,"issue_id":"bd-2o55","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Scope
